    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "DOT-DASH ZONE\nRADIO\nSTATION\nDASH-DOT ZONE\nThe directive radio beam is a series of dots and dashes broadcast continuously along the air way. When\nthe pilot hears the steady hum of dashes through his head set (see right) he knows he is following his\ntrue course.\nThe planes also have 2-way voice radio, enabling the pilot to talk to United Air Lines'\nground stations and with other planes in flight.",
      "IN FLIGHT WITH\nUNITED AIR LINES\nPOST CARD\nPlease\naddress and\nreturn to\nstewardess\nwho will\nstamp and\nmail card\nfor you.\nNO. 306\n12015.166.1695"
    ],
